{title: Old Rattler}
{artist: Mac Wiseman}
{composer: unknown}

[G]Rattler was a good old dog
As blind as he could [D7]be
But every night at suppertime
I believe that dog could [G]see
Old Rattler dreamed the other night
And I thought he'd tree'd a [D7]coon
When I come to find it out
He was barkin' at the [G]moon
Here Rattler here
Here Rattler [D7]here
Called old Rattler from the barn
Here Rattler [G]here
Grandma had a yeller hen
We set her as you [D7]know
We set her on three buzzard eggs
And hatched out one old [G]crow
Climb those Blue Ridge Mountains
They’re forty miles [D7]around
I think I’ll buy me a choppin’ axe
And cut those mountains [G]down
